==English==

===Proverb===
'''It takes two to tango''' 

# {{idiom}} Some things need the active cooperation of two parties.
#:''I can't do it by myself, and neither can you - '''it takes two to tango'''.''
#:''He started it! Well, '''it takes two to tango'''.''

